The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Chelsea outclass Wigan

London: Captain John Terry headed the winner as champions Chelsea beat Wigan Athletic 1-0 to go 12 points clear at the top of the Premier League on Saturday. Liverpool clocked up their seventh consecutive league win, beating Middlesbrough 2-0 with second-half goals. 

Chelsea are top on 43 points, with Liverpool on 31 and third-placed Manchester United (30) playing Everton on Sunday. Arsenal face Newcastle United away in Saturdays late kickoff. 

Charlton Athletic ended a run of six league and cup defeats with a 2-0 win over bottom club Sunderland, Blackburn Rovers beat West Ham 3-2. (REUTERS) 




